{"key":"processedPost-9977014","value":{"id":9977014,"first":9976985,"last":9977014,"when":1237154525,"utime":"03/16/09 01:02 AM","content":"You can use any cereal grain, but you really should pressure cook the flour/verm mix if you do.&nbsp; Brown rice flour is used because it can be steamed in a kettle, allowing new growers to get their feet wet without buying a pressure cooker.&nbsp; I haven't yet seen a grain that outperforms brown rice in cakes, so you have nothing to gain by using oats or rye, etc., but if it's all you have, AND you have a pressure cooker, it's fine to use.<br />RR","title":"Re: BRF subistutes/additives"}}